quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  54,28,"And inform<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>them that the water is to be shared between them{1}; each one should drink in turn.",footnotes:1:The water is to be shared between them and the she-camel.
  54,29,"But they called their fellow, and he dared and hamstrung<i class=""s"">(it) </i>."
  54,30,"So how were My punishment and My warnings!"
  54,31,"Indeed, We sent against them a single Shout, and they ended up like a fence-maker’s dry sticks."
  54,32,"And most surely We made the Recital{1}easy for remembrance, so is there anyone to remind himself?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  54,33,"The people of Lot disbelieved in the warnings."
  54,34,"Indeed, We sent against them a shower of stones, except for Lot’s folk–We delivered them at dawn—"
  54,35,"a blessing from Us; thus We repay whoever gives thanks."
  54,36,"And most surely he{1}had warned them of Our onslaught, but they entered into controversies about the warnings.",footnotes:1:Prophet Lot.
  54,37,"And most surely they solicited of him his guests, so We obliterated their eyes— “So taste My punishment and My warnings.”"
  54,38,"And most surely an abiding punishment came upon them in the morning—"
  54,39,"“So taste<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>My punishment and My warnings.”"
  54,40,"And most surely We made the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>easy for remembrance, so is there anyone to remind himself?"
  54,41,"And most surely the warnings came to Pharaoh’s folk—"
  54,42,"they disbelieved all Our signs. So We seized them<i class=""s"">(with) </i>the seizure of an Almighty, Invincible One."
  54,43,"“Are your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>deniers better than all those? Or do you have immunity in the Books?”"
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We, all together, will be victorious”?"
  54,45,"The multitude will be defeated, and they will turn their backs."
  54,46,"Nay, the Hour is their appointed time, and the Hour is more disastrous and more bitter."
  54,47,"Indeed, the criminals are in confusion and insanity."
  54,48,"The day when they are dragged upon their faces into the Fire: “Taste the touch of Saqar{1}.”",footnotes:1:Saqaris one of the names which the Qur’an gave to the fire of Hell.
  54,49,"Indeed, We have created everything in due measure."
